DUE LOANS ARE LOANS THAT ARE CONTRACTUALLY PAST DUE 90 DAYS OR MORE AS TO PRINCIPAL OR INTEREST PAYMENTS. RESTRUCTURED LOANS AND CARD MEMBER RECEIVABLES ARE THOSE THAT MEET THE DEFINITION OF TDR.

